data.chText: 庸俗的；粗俗的；粗野的；不雅的
data.enText: not having or showing good taste; not polite, elegant or well behaved

data.chText: 她觉得他们的笑声和吵吵闹闹的游戏趣味低下，俗不可耐。
data.enText: She found their laughter and noisy games coarse and rather vulgar.

simple_means.memory_skill: vulg 人群 + ar …的，有…性质的 → 大众的；粗俗的

example: full of language so vulgar it should have been edited

tr: being or characteristic of or appropriate to everyday language
example: the vulgar tongue of the masses
the technical and vulgar names for an animal species

tr: of or associated with the great masses of people
example: the common people in those days suffered greatly
behavior that branded him as common

tr: lacking refinement or cultivation or taste
example: he had coarse manners but a first-rate mind
behavior that branded him as common
an untutored and uncouth human being
an uncouth soldier--a real tough guy
appealing to the vulgar taste for violence
the vulgar display of the newly rich

value.def: If you describe something as vulgar, you think it is in bad taste or of poor artistic quality.

example.ex: I think it's a very vulgar house...
example.tran: 我觉得这所房子很俗气。

example.ex: The film is tasteless, vulgar and even badly shot.
example.tran: 这部电影毫无品位、庸俗不堪，甚至可以说拍得很烂。

value.tran: 粗俗的;庸俗的;俗气的;不雅的

example.ex: I hate the vulgarity of this room.
example.tran: 我讨厌这个房间的庸俗劲儿。

value.def: If you describe pictures, gestures, or remarks as vulgar, you dislike them because they refer to sex or parts of the body in a rude way that you find unpleasant.

example.ex: The women laughed coarsely at some vulgar jokes...
example.tran: 那些女人听了一些下流的笑话后粗俗地大笑。

value.tran: （图画、姿势或言论）下流的，猥亵的

example.ex: There's  a good deal of vulgarity.

value.def: If you describe a person or their behaviour as vulgar, you mean that they lack taste or behave rudely.

example.ex: He was a vulgar old man, but he never swore in front of a woman...
example.tran: 他是个粗鲁的老头，但他从来不在女人面前说脏话。

value.tran: 粗俗的;无礼的;粗鄙的;粗鲁的

example.ex: It's his vulgarity that I can't take.
example.tran: 我不能容忍的是他的粗鄙。

trans: 民间拉丁语(罗马帝国西部使用的拉丁口语)
